---

End-to-End Flow (Condensed)

1. User initiates BG vetting from host platform


2. Host platform authenticates and issues platform token


3. BG Auth Service validates request and issues BG session token


4. BG frontend loads and fetches BG data via BG backend


5. User reviews / edits BG


6. On submit, BG backend validates token and forwards BG text


7. Host platform advances journey to next screen




---

Security Design Principles

Identity owned by host platform

Authorization scoped per BG

Short-lived, revocable tokens

Zero trust between frontend and backend

Full auditability



---

Success Metrics (Optional but Strong)

0 unauthorized BG submissions

<15 min session expiry enforcement

100% submit idempotency

Zero credential leakage incidents



---

Out of Scope

User login / password management

Journey navigation control

Platform authentication logic



---

Final One-Liner (Exec Friendly)

> â€œThe BG vetting solution integrates as a secure, BG-scoped micro-frontend using short-lived authorization tokens, while identity and journey orchestration remain with the host platform.â€




